    {
      "_key": "d7d8ae104acf",
      "_type": "block",
      "children": [
        {
          "_key": "8892f1aaa72e",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "The Instant series of books are not “bible” books. They do not tell you everything you want to know but are afraid to ask, nor do they go into endless details about why things work the way they do. They facilitate accomplishing core tasks quickly, using workflows the authors have found the most practical."
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [],
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "_key": "72f7ad734877",
      "_type": "block",
      "children": [
        {
          "_key": "44e05dcc7bd3",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "We have tried to fill this book with enough basics to get you productive quickly and enough advanced tips and techniques to keep you exploring new directions. You don’t have to read Instant ACID cover to cover to understand it. It is written more like a task-oriented reference that you can use to learn the areas that interest you. It is very visual and to the point. We hope you get as much out of reading it as we did writing it. If you have any questions, you can always find us on the "
        },
        {
          "_key": "d380ce90c336",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [
            "f11a29185cb0"
          ],
          "text": "Magix Forums"
        },
        {
          "_key": "d3c8cec9abc6",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": " (John Rofrano is JohnnyRoy, and Iacobus is Iacobus)."
        }
